0.196 g
297.6377952755905767 391.1813385826770855 Td
(B\) Coordination improves) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 8.5 Tf
9.7749999999999986 TL
0.196 g
56.6929133858267775 378.4254330708660632 Td
(C\) Authority is undermined, discipline is in jeopardy, order) Tj
T* (disturbed, and stability threatened) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 8.5 Tf
9.7749999999999986 TL
0.196 g
297.6377952755905767 378.4254330708660632 Td
(D\) Decentralisation is achieved) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 8 Tf
9.1999999999999993 TL
0.086 0.639 0.29 rg
56.6929133858267775 362.8348818897637216 Td
(Answer: C\) Authority is undermined, discipline is in jeopardy, order disturbed, and stability threatened. Fayol gave immense importance to having only one boss to prevent confusion) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 9 Tf
10.3499999999999996 TL
0.051 g
56.6929133858267775 331.6537795275589815 Td
(Q190. What is the primary difference in the aim between Unity of Command and Unity of Direction?) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 8.5 Tf
9.7749999999999986 TL
0.196 g
56.6929133858267775 311.8112598425195756 Td
(A\) Unity of command prevents overlapping of activities, while) Tj
T* (Unity of direction prevents dual subordination) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 8.5 Tf
9.7749999999999986 TL
0.196 g
297.6377952755905767 311.8112598425195756 Td
(B\) Unity of command affects the entire organisation, while) Tj
T* (Unity of direction affects an individual) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 8.5 Tf
9.7749999999999986 TL
0.196 g
56.6929133858267775 286.2994488188975311 Td
(C\) Unity of command prevents dual subordination, while) Tj
T* (Unity of direction prevents overlapping of activities) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 8.5 Tf
9.7749999999999986 TL
0.196 g
297.6377952755905767 286.2994488188975311 Td
(D\) There is no difference; they are synonymous) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 8 Tf
9.1999999999999993 TL
0.086 0.639 0.29 rg
56.6929133858267775 270.7088976377951894 Td
(Answer: C\) Unity of command prevents dual subordination, while Unity of direction prevents overlapping of activities. Unity of command ensures one boss per employee, while unity of direction ensures one head and one plan for activities with the same objective) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 9 Tf
10.3499999999999996 TL
0.051 g
56.6929133858267775 239.5277952755905062 Td
(Q191. Fayol's principle of "Subordination of Individual Interest to General Interest" implies that:) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 8.5 Tf
9.7749999999999986 TL
0.196 g
56.6929133858267775 219.6852755905511003 Td
(A\) The company should pay maximum possible salaries to) Tj
T* (everyone regardless of output) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 8.5 Tf
9.7749999999999986 TL
0.196 g
297.6377952755905767 219.6852755905511003 Td
(B\) The larger interests of the workers, stakeholders, and the) Tj
T* (company should supersede the personal motives of any one) Tj
T* (individual) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 8.5 Tf
9.7749999999999986 TL
0.196 g
56.6929133858267775 181.4175590551179766 Td
(C\) Employees must completely sacrifice their personal lives) Tj
T* (for the company) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 8.5 Tf
9.7749999999999986 TL
0.196 g
297.6377952755905767 181.4175590551179766 Td
(D\) Managers should prioritise their family benefits over the) Tj
T* (company) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 8 Tf
9.1999999999999993 TL
0.086 0.639 0.29 rg
56.6929133858267775 153.0711023622046696 Td
(Answer: B\) The larger interests of the workers, stakeholders, and the company should supersede the personal motives of any one individual. A manager can ensure this by exhibiting exemplary behaviour) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 9 Tf
10.3499999999999996 TL
0.051 g
56.6929133858267775 121.8899999999998727 Td
(Q192. Which principle states that the concentration of decision-making authority must be appropriately balanced) Tj
T* (with subordinate involvement?) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 8.5 Tf
9.7749999999999986 TL
0.196 g
56.6929133858267775 87.8742519685038133 Td
(A\) Centralisation and Decentralisation) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 8.5 Tf
9.7749999999999986 TL
0.196 g
297.6377952755905767 87.8742519685038133 Td
(B\) Scalar Chain) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 8.5 Tf
9.7749999999999986 TL
0.196 g
56.6929133858267775 75.1183464566928478 Td
(C\) Unity of Direction) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 8.5 Tf
9.7749999999999986 TL
0.196 g
297.6377952755905767 75.1183464566928478 Td
(D\) Esprit De Corps) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 8 Tf
9.1999999999999993 TL
0.086 0.639 0.29 rg
56.6929133858267775 59.5277952755905062 Td
(Answer: A\) Centralisation and Decentralisation. Large organisations generally have more decentralisation than small organisations, but a balance of both is required) Tj
ET
